==Controversies==
{{undue weight|section|date=October 2015}}

Dinesh Singh's style of functioning has been termed by a section of Delhi University teachers as "authoritarian" and "megalomaniac".<ref>{{cite news | author =TNN | title =Delhi University Teachers Association bays for Dinesh Singh's blood | url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Delhi-University-Teachers-Association-bays-for-Dinesh-Singhs-blood/articleshow/20022356.cms | newspaper = Times of India | date = 13 May 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author =SNN | title =DUTA wants action against 'autocratic' VC | url = http://www.thestatesman.com/news/delhi/duta-wants-action-against-autocratic-vc/96559.html | newspaper = The Statesman | date = 13 Oct 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author = | title = DU VC acting like `terrorist`, has taken university `hostage`: Nandita Narain| url = http://zeenews.india.com/news/delhi/du-vc-acting-like-terrorist-has-taken-university-hostage-nandita-narain_942553.html | newspaper = Zee News | date = 25 June 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author =ANI | title = Dinesh Singh acting like terrorist, has taken university hostage, says President of Delhi University Teacher's Association| url = http://www.dnaindia.com/delhi/report-dinesh-singh-acting-like-terrorist-has-taken-university-hostage-says-president-of-delhi-university-teacher-s-association-1997728 | newspaper = DNA | date = 25 June 2014 }}</ref> President of the Delhi University & College Karamchari (Worker) Union (DUCKU), publicly made an allegation that the Vice-Chancellor had created a terror-like atmosphere in Delhi University as there is absolutely no space for dissent.<ref name="Namita Nair, Indrani Dasgupta">{{cite news | author       =Namita Nair, Indrani Dasgupta| title        =  Dissent suppressed in DU by ‘feudal, autocratic’ VC | url          =  http://www.sunday-guardian.com/news/dissent-suppressed-in-du-by-feudal-autocratic-vc| newspaper    = [[Sunday Guardian]]  | date         = 20 April 2013 }}</ref> An elected member of the DU Executive Council claimed that, in an attempt to stifle any voice of dissent in the university, the VC allowed violence to happen against a senior professor at the Shri Ram College of Commerce.<ref name="Namita Nair, Indrani Dasgupta"/> Bhaskaracharya College of Applied Sciences principal Manoj Khanna resigned from his position after calling Delhi University Vice-Chancellor Dinesh Singh’s way of functioning as "autocratic". However, spokesperson of the University, Malay Neerav denied Manoj Khanna's allegations that colleges were forced by the Vice Chancellor to submit false affidavits to All-India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) for getting approval to run BTech courses.<ref>{{cite news | author       =Heena Kausar| title        =  Calling DU V-C autocratic, officiating principal resigns| url          = http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/calling-du-vc-autocratic-officiating-principal-resigns/article7136350.ece| newspaper    = The Hindu  | date         = 24 April 2015 }}</ref> Other high level administrators like Pro-Vice Chancellor and Dean of Examination had also resigned during the tenure of Dinesh Singh on the grounds of personal reasons but citing sources in the Delhi university, newspapers reported that these officials resigned due to differences with officials of the Vice-Chancellor's team.<ref>{{cite news | author       = Manash Pratim Gohain| title        =  Delhi University’s pro-VC quits office| url          = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Delhi-Universitys-pro-VC-quits-office/articleshow/18740677.cms| newspaper    = The Times of India  | date         = 1 March 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author       =Vijetha S.N.| title        =  Delhi University Pro V-C resigns| url          = http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-otherstates/delhi-university-pro-vc-resigns/article4468313.ece| newspaper    = The Hindu  | date         = 2 March 2013 }}</ref>

His tenure has been controversial and he has been accused of financial and administrative irregularities.<ref name=tenureend>{{cite news | author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> | date = 27 Oct 2015 | title = Dinesh Singh's controversial tenure as DU VC to end tomorrow | url =  http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/dinesh-singh-s-controversial-tenure-as-du-vc-to-end-tomorrow-115102701523_1.html | newspaper = Business Standard | location =  | access-date  =  }}</ref> A ‘White Paper’ released by Delhi University Teachers’ Association (DUTA) alleged financial and administrative irregularities in functioning of Delhi University, like diversion of OBC funds for purchase of laptops or flagging off ‘Gyanodaya Express’.<ref name=jan1mp>{{cite news | author =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> | title = HRD ministry questions DU V-C’s conduct | url = http://www.millenniumpost.in/NewsContent.aspx?NID=90708 | newspaper = Millennium Post | date = 1 January 2015 }}</ref>  The Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India, after approval of the President of India (who is also the Visitor of Delhi University) issued a showcause notice to Singh regarding these allegations.<ref name=endgame>{{cite news | last = Mukul | first = Akshaya | date = 19 March 2015 | title = Endgame begins for DU VC as govt serves show-cause notice on him | url =  http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Endgame-begins-for-DU-VC-as-govt-serves-show-cause-notice-on-him/articleshow/46615991.cms | newspaper = Times of India | location = | access-date =  }}</ref> He is the first Delhi University Vice-Chancellor who has been served a show-cause notice to be removed from the post in the 93-year-old history.<ref>{{cite news | author       = | title = Sailing through 'eventful tenure' DU VC Dinesh Singh demits office | url =  http://zeenews.india.com/news/education/sailing-through-eventful-tenure-du-vc-dinesh-singh-demits-office_1815715.html| newspaper = Zee News  | date = 28 October 2015 }}</ref><ref name="endgame"/> Singh responded to the showcause notice denying every charge but HRD ministry turned down his request for withdrawing showcause notice.<ref>{{cite news | last = Press Trust Of India | first = | date = 10 April 2015 | title = HRD min turns down DU VC's request for withdrawing showcause | url =  http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/hrd-min-turns-down-du-vc-s-request-for-withdrawing-showcause-115041001061_1.html | newspaper = Business Standard | location     =  | access-date  =  }}</ref> Noted Academics including ex-President of the Indian National Science Academy, Krishan Lal, former Director General of the Council for Scientific and Industrial Research, SK Brahmachari, Keki N Daruwallla, ex-Vice President of the Indian Academy of Sciences and a host of academics from JNU, Jamia and Banaras Hindu University and Ex-DU Vice-Chancellor "backed" Prof. Dinesh Singh raising concern over the manner in which, "the autonomy of the university was being compromised".  http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-academics-and-ex-du-vice-chancellor-back-dinesh-singh-2076233

The government decided not to process his reply to the showcause notice as he had barely few months left in his tenure and few senior Cabinet ministers pleaded for no action against him in order for him to finish his full term.<ref>{{cite news | author = Akshaya Mukul | title = VC's name dropped from Prez trip | url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/VCs-name-dropped-from-Prez-trip/articleshow/49176265.cms | newspaper = Times of India | date = 1 October 2015 }}</ref>

The HRD ministry, on 7 October 2015, requested the Visitor to send Dinesh Singh on 'forced leave' on the charge that Dinesh Singh tried to derail the process of appointment of his successor.<ref>{{cite news | author       = Akshaya Mukul | title        =  President 'not convinced', HRD ministry withdraws file on 'forced leave' for DU VC Dinesh Singh | url          =  http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/President-not-convinced-HRD-ministry-withdraws-file-on-forced-leave-for-DU-VC-Dinesh-Singh/articleshow/49266864.cms | newspaper = Times of India  | date = 8 October 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author = Abantika Ghosh , Ritika Chopra | title = Put Delhi University Vice Chancellor on compulsory wait, HRD tells President | url = http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/put-delhi-university-v-c-on-compulsory-wait-hrd-tells-president/ | newspaper = Indian Express | date = 8 October 2015 }}</ref> However, the HRD ministry had to withdraw the request as the Visitor Pranab Mukherjee was not convinced if the DU VC should be punished with barely 20 days left of his term.<ref>{{cite news | author       =  Akshaya Mukul  | title        =  President 'not convinced', HRD ministry withdraws file on 'forced leave' for DU VC Dinesh Singh | url          =  http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/President-not-convinced-HRD-ministry-withdraws-file-on-forced-leave-for-DU-VC-Dinesh-Singh/articleshow/49266864.cms | newspaper    = Times of India  | date = 8 October 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author = Ritika Chopra | title =  DU VC Dinesh Singh: Resignation only graceful end to his controversial tenure | url =  http://indianexpress.com/article/explained/du-vc-dinesh-singh-resignation-only-graceful-end-to-his-controversial-tenure/ | newspaper = Indian Express | date = 8 October 2015 }}</ref> The Visitor asked Dinesh Singh not to continue for a single day beyond the last day of his term.<ref>{{cite news | author = manash pratim gohain  | title  =  DU VC to stay in office till end of tenure| url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/DU-VC-to-stay-in-office-till-end-of-tenure/articleshow/49294690.cms | newspaper = Times of India | date = 9 October 2015 }}</ref> However, Dinesh Singh denied the charge of intentionally derailing the process of appointment of his successor and asserted that he will not continue a day beyond his tenure as is being speculated.<ref>{{cite news | author = | title = Prez asks Delhi Univ to send new name for VC search panel | url = http://zeenews.india.com/news/delhi/prez-asks-delhi-univ-to-send-new-name-for-vc-search-panel_1808173.html | newspaper = Zee News  | date = 9 October 2015 }}</ref> In spite of just 20-odd days left for the completion of his term, a large number of teachers and students came out to protest in front of the Vice Regal Lodge demanding his ouster.
<ref name="Clamour for ouster of Singh grows">{{cite news | author =  | title =  Clamour for ouster of Singh grows| url = http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31808&articlexml=Clamour-for-ouster-of-Singh-grows-10102015007006 | newspaper = Times of India  | date = 10 October 2015 }}</ref> Not only did the activists of National Democratic Teachers' Front and Academics for Action and Development (Rathi) protest against Dinesh Singh.<ref name="Clamour for ouster of Singh grows"/> but the demand for the removal of Dinesh Singh has seen the archrivals Democratic Teachers' Front (DTF) and Academics for Action and Development (AAD) to join anti-VC protests by Delhi University Teachers Association.  J Khuntiya, chairman, AAD (Rathi) alleged that the delay has been intentional to ensure that Umesh Rai, a member of the team of Dinesh Singh becomes eligible for selection.<ref>{{cite news | author = manash pratim gohain =  | title = Teachers slam varsity's 'mistake' of choosing ex-Isro chief for post| url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/Teachers-slam-varsitys-mistake-of-choosing-ex-Isro-chief-for-post/articleshow/49294714.cms | newspaper = Times of India  | date = 10 October 2015 }}</ref> One of the names included by Dinesh Singh in the search committee for the selection of new Vice-Chancellor is Vinod Rai.    
<ref>{{cite news | author = anubhuti vishnoi  | title = Delhi University has to wait for its new VC after K Kasturirangan dropped from search panel | url = http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/delhi-university-has-to-wait-for-its-new-vc-after-k-kasturirangan-dropped-from-search-panel/articleshow/49264483.cms | newspaper = Economic Times | date = 8 October 2015 }}</ref>

DUTA has also recently charged Singh with plagiarism and has sought investigation into these plagiarism charges against him.<ref>{{cite news | last = S.N. | first = Vijetha | date = 10 October 2014 | title = DUTA seeks investigation into plagiarism charges against V-C | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/duta-seeks-investigation-into-plagiarism-charges-against-vc/article6487568.ece | newspaper =  The Hindu }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author  =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> | title = DU teachers seek probe against VC | url = http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/delhi/du-teachers-seek-probe-against-vc/ | newspaper = Indian Express | date = 9 October 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author =<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> | title = Investigate Plagiarism Charges against DU VC | url =  http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-PTQJ5MgMnRg/VDf3UunNBaI/AAAAAAAADaI/zp7FMS-5aso/s1600/DH_9Oct.jpg | newspaper = Deccan Herald | date = }}</ref> 

Singh was instrumental in initiating Four Year Undergraduate Program (FYUP) which met with a lot of resistance from different quarters, after which the programme was scrapped as per the directives of the University Grant Commission(UGC) .<ref>
{{cite news | last         = Pratim Gohain  | first        =  Manash | date         = 27 June 2014 | title        = Delhi University rolls back four-year undergraduate programme, VC Dinesh Singh says  | url          =  http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/Delhi-University-rolls-back-four-year-undergraduate-programme-VC-Dinesh-Singh-says/articleshow/37314711.cms | newspaper    = Times of India   }}
</ref> Thereafter, Singh announced his resignation <ref>{{cite news | last = Pratim Gohain | first = Manash | date = 24 June 2014| title = FYUP row: Delhi University VC Dinesh Singh resigns| url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/FYUP-row-Delhi-University-VC-Dinesh-Singh-resigns/articleshow/37118148.cms | newspaper = Times of India }}</ref> but later retracted it.<ref>{{cite news | last = S.N. | first = Vijetha | date = 24 June 2014 | title = Confusion over DU VC’s resignation | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/confusion-over-du-vcs-resignation/article6145392.ece| newspaper = The Hindu }}</ref>

