'''Krista Sutton''' (born March 29, 1970) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[actress]] who has worked in [[television]], [[film|movie]]s and [[theatre]]. She is also an acting [[teacher]]. She grew up in [[Toronto]] but currently lives in [[New York City]]. She is best known for her leading role in the improvisational drama [[Train 48]].
